<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-8702] LatencyMetrics is reporting total latency in nanoseconds rather than microseconds</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8702</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know if this is the desired behaviour but all the comments in the code indicate that it should be reporting microseconds. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A single write shows the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;WriteLatency
------------
Count: 1
Min: 315.853
Max: 379.022

WriteTotalLatency
-----------------
Count: 339667
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In LatencyMetrics:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/** Total latency in micro sec */&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; Counter totalLatency;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
